 :tx/rationale "UAQ INSIGHT 18: WITNESS SUGGESTION IN STATUS OUTPUT — THE CONCRETE UX. When braid status runs and unwitnessed INVs exist with name-matchable tests (scan_source already identifies these), the status output should include a suggested witness pairing as a scored context block. FORMAT: 'suggest: test_merge_commutativity → INV-MERGE-001 (alpha=0.34) — confirm: braid witness confirm INV-MERGE-001 test_merge_commutativity'. This is a ContextBlock with: kind=ObservationKind::WitnessSuggestion (future, use ContextBlock for now), impact = F(S) improvement from one more witnessed INV = 1/total_unwitnessed (normalized), cost = tokens for the suggestion line (~15 tokens), alpha = impact/cost. The agent confirms with ONE COMMAND: braid witness confirm. The witness count goes up. F(S) goes up. The acquisition function calibrates from the confirmation. Next session, better pairings proposed. IMPLEMENTATION: In UAQ-3 (context block scoring), add a new block source: unwitnessed_inv_suggestions(). This function: (1) Gets unwitnessed INVs from witness_gaps(store). (2) For each, searches test function names in trace data for keyword overlap with the INV name/falsification. (3) Ranks by match quality. (4) Returns top-1 as a ContextBlock with AcquisitionScore. (5) The block competes with all other blocks for budget. If it survives, the agent sees the suggestion. If budget cuts it, the INV stays unwitnessed until alpha increases (maybe next session when other blocks have decayed via novelty). IMPLEMENTATION COST: ~100 LOC in context.rs + ~20 LOC for braid witness confirm subcommand. SPEC: INV-WITNESS-011, ADR-FOUNDATION-025, ADR-FOUNDATION-028."
